node.text:
The fine folks at @lastdropbeerfestival featured our Dole Whip-inspired smoothie-style berliner in their festival last Saturday and shot some great footage in our new cellar space!

If you scored #TropicalHideaway cans out in their first shot at limited distribution today, give this clip a listen and make sure you’re storing those cans cold, drinking ‘em fresh, and giving them a proper tiki-shake before you open and pour! 

(Also, huge-huge-huge congrats to the Cast Members bringing #Disneyland back to life today! Come grab a draft beer at 20% off today [and everyday!] with your TWDC ID!)

🐢
🐢
🐢

node.text:
DOUBLE CAN DROP: We've got two beautifully crisp, ultra-traditional lagers to battle this heatwave and get you right into the Oktoberfest-headspace!

🥨 #Orctoberfest: Traditional German-Style Festbier • 6.25% ABV • Barke Pils, Vienna, Munich 1, Caramunich, and Acidulated malts and hopped with Magnum, Tettnang, and Mittelfruh hops. Malty sweetness with a hint of toast met by a soft, balanced bitterness.

🇩🇪 Traditional German-Style Pilsner • 4.25% ABV • Pilsner, Dextra Pils, and Acidulated malts and hopped with Tettnang, Tradition, and Mittlefrueh. Crisp, light, and noble.

📱 • Order beer-to-go at the link in our profile!⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
CAN DROP: #BirthdayBoiDarwin - Amarillo-Hopped West Coast IPA • 6.1% ABV • We're celebrating the 11th birthday of the inimitable @bobvreeland's mini-dachshund, Darwin! 

To know Bob is to know amarillo hops, and their sweet orange citrus flavors are on bold display in this iteration of our growing pet-birthday can releases. (Why even have a brewery if you're not putting your pets on your beer labels?)

Aromas of pine and candied citrus bound into a resinous initial hop bite on the palate that rolls into a mild orange-pith finish. Light-bodied and easy drinking at 6.1% ABV.

🧑‍🔬 • @sunsettrivia kicks off at 6:30pm! It's free!
📱 • Order beer-to-go at the link in our profile!⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

Pick-up is open and runs through 8/22!

We’re open from 12:00-10:00pm with @octacos.1!

node.text:
Fellow Innovators! It’s the proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale day for #FOMO2021!

We've been iterating #FOMO into perfection over the last five years with the incomparable team at @mostracoffee, and we're delighted to finally offer it to you in bottles!

This liquid is a complex blend pulled from barrels filled throughout 2018 and 2020. FOMO 2021 is a 2/3 to 1/3 double-to-single mash base, aged with Madagascar vanilla beans then debarrelled and steeped on 80lbs of Mostra-roasted coffee beans from El Salvador.

Aromas of coffee tinted with baking chocolate, dulce de leche, and crispy corner pieces of brownie swirl onto the palate through waves of rich, creamy vanilla. At a 2/3 ratio of double mash, this liquid stains the glass and lingers on the palate with a chewy caramel lacing and the faintest hint of peanut butter cups from Mostra's extraordinary "#FOMOBlend" of coffee beans.
⁣⁣
=============== SALE DETAILS ===============⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• Tickets go live at the top link in our profile at 12:00pm, limit 1pp.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
• If you've already purchased bottles in our local-access direct sale, you're still welcome to participate in today's Eventbrite sale.⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
• Proxy pickup is welcome in our Eventbrite sales! ⁣⁣⁣⁣Proxy registration takes place during the ticket registration, though you may edit details through the link in your confirmation email afterward.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• You will need the following information to register a proxy: Their Full Name, Date of Birth, and email address.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ Your proxy MUST show ID that matches these information fields to retrieve bottles.
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
=============== Pick Up Details =========⁣======⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• Bottles are immediately available for retrieval at the brewery from 8/8- 8/22.
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ ⁣
• Again, proxy pick-ups are permitted but must be registered through Eventbrite. You are able to adjust your proxy post-purchase through the link in your confirmation email. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• We strongly recommend picking up on weekdays from 6-10pm. Saturday/Sunday crowds are inevitable, avoid them as best you can! ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
#StasisProject #BottleLogic #BottleLogicBrewing #BarrelAgedBeer

node.text:
@scoopsontap is scooping seven epic #StasisProject-infused ice creams from 12:00 - 9:00pm, and they've brought the big guns today:

Their #PaisleyCaveComplex ice cream drew a fanatic crowd at #WeekOfLogic2019, so Sam & Brian raided their bottle stash to return with a single bin of this mythical flavor.

PCC: The Ice Cream was infused with our Bourbon Barrel Aged Blueberry S'Mores Imperial Stout, then loaded with mountains of toasted marshmallows, a fresh swirl of Oregon-grown Highbush blueberries, and topped off with fair-trade Ecuadorian cacao nibs for the perfect bitter dark chocolate contrast to this luxuriously complex flavor.

This one's moving fast -- swing by soon! 🍦🍦🍦

node.text:
Fellow Innovators! Late last year we blazed through an unexpected hit of a canned sweet stout release -- there were astronauts and maple syrup! There were grizzly bears and blueberries and DeLoreans! There was #NoTimeToExplain!

We've applied that absurdly delicious finishing treatment to a mix of Fundamental Observation barrels filled throughout 2018, 2019, and 2020, then blended with a chewy, lactose-based sweet stout for a liquid that can only rightly be called: #MoreTimeToExplain!

Huge aromas of ripe blueberry and sweet maple syrup deliver waves of blueberry pancake-stuffed nostalgia. Bright blueberry opens the palate then oaky vanilla from beans and barrel hit mid-palate, tempering the sweetness of a long, maple-rich finish. Lactose delivers a creamy mouthfeel on a velvety base that drinks like the Sunday morning of a three-day weekend.
⁣⁣
Local-access bottles go live at 11:45am on Toast, limit 6pp. Orders must be retrieved on the day they're placed and are not available for proxy pick-up. Toast sales culminate at sell-through or at 10:00pm on Saturday 8/14; any remaining inventory will be sold in a proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale on 8/15.
⁣⁣

node.text:
People of Earth! We're unbelievably stoked to welcome @scoopsontap to the Tasting Room for three days of pop-up ice cream service! 

Join us for fresh scoops and packed pints of their legendary beer-infused ice cream, available while supplies last throughout the weekend: 

• Friday: 4 - 9pm
• Saturday: 12 - 9pm
• Sunday: 12 - 8pm

Here's a peek at their incredible flavor line-up:

🔬 • Salted FO - Argentinean dulce de leche ice cream infused with #FundamentalObservation2021 and sea salt.

☕️ • FOMO - Costa Rican coffee ice cream infused with #FOMO2021 and Madagascar vanilla with a swirl of dulce de leche and fudge brownies.

🍍 • Broken Blender (Plant Based) - #BrokenBlender2021-infused coconut ice cream with nutmeg, Madagascar Vanilla, and swirls of Valencia orange and Abacaxi pineapples.

🔥 • Arcane Rituals - #ArcaneRituals2021-infused ice cream with pounds of freshly made butterscotch, English butter toffee, and sea salt. 

🍒 • On the Flipside - Abacaxi pineapple and Montmorency cherry ice cream infused with #OnTheFlipside.

⚫️ • Degree of Motion - Madagascar vanilla ice cream infused with #DegreeOfMotion2021 and loaded with chocolate sandwich cookies crumbles.

🏔 • Paisley Cave Complex - #PaisleyCaveComplex2020-infused ice cream with pounds of toasted marshmallows, Ecuadorian cacao nibs, and a swirl of fresh blueberries. [SATURDAY ONLY!]

We're open from 12:00 - 10:00pm with @theberlintruck!

The fermentors are standing! The brites are bubbling! The new 30bbl Prospero brewhouse is dialed in and cranking! The only thing our production expansion is missing is YOU! 

We're looking to add an experienced brewer to our award-winning team of professional innovators. Hands-on brewing experience in a production brewery is preferred, however, the right candidate may be able to substitute substantial homebrewing experience or certified brewing education.

Check out the detailed position posting and apply through the link in our profile!
